body": "```\r\n  --fetch-all           this option has no effect and will be removed in a\r\n                        future version. When no siblings are given, an all-\r\n                        sibling update will be performed.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat means that `update` cannot acknowledge a potentially carefully crafted git configuration that \"pulls\" from a default location. I either have to go explicit with `--name`, or endure a fetch of (potentially many) undesired remotes.\r\n\r\nDiscovered when wondering we no fetch progress is reported: https://github.com/datalad/datalad/pull/4080#issuecomment-578483030", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4086/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4086/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}